> Au Poivre is a staple on french bistro menus for a reason, it's delicious! This dish may sound fancy but It's simply a peppercorn crusted steak that is seared, creating a delicious zingy crust that pairs perfectly with the juicy meat. Then it's topped with an elegant peppery sauce that is rich with flavor from our demi-glace and finished with butter. Served with golden potato wedges and roasted green beans, it's a complete elegant meal. Bonus points for making you feel like you just landed in Pari!

== Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce}, if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP. Place @Black Peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in a #zip-close bag{}; crush with a #rolling pin{} or a heavy pan. Thinly slice @Chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until lightly browned, about ~{15%minutes} (we'll add more to the sheet then).

Once potatoes have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add green beans to a second #baking sheet{}.) Carefully push potatoes to one side. Carefully toss green beans on opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Continue roasting until veggies are browned and tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

== Beef ==

Meanwhile, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and let rest for ~{5%minutes}. Wash out pan.

== Sauce ==

Melt 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @Beef Demi-Glace{1}, @water{¼%cup}, and 1 tsp crushed peppercorns (be sure to measure). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in another 1 TBSP butter, half the chives, and any resting juices from beef. Season with @salt{} and more peppercorns, if desired.

== To Serve ==

Divide potatoes, green beans, and beef between #plates{}. Top beef with sauce. Sprinkle with remaining chives.